Decisions
---------
- Step 07 branched from origin/main (not the step-06 branch, which was squash-
  merged via PR #7) so the PR diff shows only Step 07.
- LastSync advances only on a fully successful fetch+upsert; partial results are
  persisted but do not advance the window (self-healing incremental sync).
- Gmail uses a plain errgroup (no derived context) for partial-result harvest;
  the documented process-wide Gmail Get ceiling is maxConc(8) x
  fetchConcurrency(8) = 64, acceptable for a personal reader's few accounts.
- Spinner runs during the initial sweep only (inflight counter); periodic sweeps
  refresh the "synced N ago" timestamp without re-lighting it (a sweep-start
  signal for a per-tick spinner is left for later).
- No native_id / schema change; engine does not import the UI (emits plain
  Results adapted by the UI).
